external_knowledge:
- Average rating is a measure of the overall satisfaction of customers with a product, with higher ratings indicating higher satisfaction; 
- Sentiment scores represent the emotions or opinions expressed in reviews, with higher scores indicating more positive sentiments; 
- Reviewer performance is crucial in determining the credibility of reviews, with reviewers having higher average sentiment scores per review being considered more trustworthy; 
- The latest metric values and names provide insights into the current trends and performance of products.

sql:
SELECT reviewer_name, email, review_count
FROM reviewers
ORDER BY review_count DESC;
